<h3>What is CRUD?</h3>
<p>
    CRUD is an acronym that stands for the four basic operations of any
    persistent storage system:
</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Create</strong>: Add new records to the database.</li>
    <li><strong>Read</strong>: Retrieve and view existing records.</li>
    <li><strong>Update</strong>: Modify existing records.</li>
    <li><strong>Delete</strong>: Remove records permanently.</li>
</ul>
<p>This application implements these functionalities to create a simple, user-friendly data management solution.</p>

